snippet: Since Ethiopian troops crossed the border in November, they have captured Beledweyne and Baidoa from the Shabab rebels.
abstract: African Union says Ethiopia, which has deployed hundred of troops in Somalia to fight Islamist insurgents, will withdraw them by the end of April.
lead_paragraph: Since Ethiopian troops crossed the border in November, they have captured Beledweyne and Baidoa from the Shabab rebels.

headline.main: Somalia: Ethiopia to Withdraw Troops by End of April
